WEBVTT

00:11.311 --> 00:13.281
I've never met Glen
or Beth A before.

00:13.381 --> 00:17.217
Beth A is Irene's replacement
when she went and got married.

00:17.318 --> 00:18.652
Glen, I remember going,

00:18.751 --> 00:20.788
"That's who they chose
to replace me?"

00:20.888 --> 00:23.291
-Nice to see you.
-Yeah, you too.

00:23.390 --> 00:24.391
[Irene] Incoming message.

00:24.492 --> 00:27.094
Don't do that! I swear to God!

00:27.195 --> 00:32.100
Y'all did not know that I was
popping laxatives, throwing up.

00:32.200 --> 00:33.667
I was dealing with some shit!

00:33.767 --> 00:36.969
You sitting here laughing,
it's still not funny.

00:37.070 --> 00:40.841
And the two people who came to
talk to me don't even know me.

00:40.941 --> 00:43.176
I wanted to go into the kitchen
when you went into the kitchen,

00:43.277 --> 00:44.545
but I was like...

00:44.645 --> 00:45.978
Girl, don't come up here
with that bullshit.

00:46.079 --> 00:49.682
I felt very hurt,
because y'all don't give a fuck.

00:49.783 --> 00:51.185
That's not true.

00:51.284 --> 00:53.686
I don't let people in,
and there's a reason for that.

00:59.826 --> 01:01.161
[Tami] This is the true story...

01:01.262 --> 01:02.563
* True story! *

01:02.662 --> 01:04.097
[Jon] Of seven strangers...

01:04.198 --> 01:06.634
[Beth S] Picked to move
back into a house...

01:06.733 --> 01:08.402
[Irene] And have
their lives taped again.

01:08.501 --> 01:09.403
[David] Guess who's back.

01:09.503 --> 01:10.638
Find out what happens...

01:10.737 --> 01:11.971
[Beth A]
When people stop being polite...

01:12.072 --> 01:13.340
[Glen] And start getting real.

01:13.441 --> 01:14.742
[man] Westside!

01:18.346 --> 01:21.781
[light music playing]

01:31.959 --> 01:33.694
-...her feelings.
-Right.

01:35.396 --> 01:36.697
[Irene] Yeah.

01:45.004 --> 01:47.007
[Beth S]
Tami, fuck these cameras.

01:47.106 --> 01:49.643
-I care about your feelings.
-[Tami] It's no problem, Beth.

01:49.742 --> 01:52.746
[Beth S] I'm sorry if you felt
like I was not there for you.

01:52.846 --> 01:54.615
-It's no problem.
-'Cause it really took...

01:54.715 --> 01:56.150
You know, you were so brave.

01:56.250 --> 01:58.319
[Tami] I'm telling you honestly,
don't worry about it.

01:58.418 --> 02:00.853
I'm used to people
not giving a fuck.

02:01.822 --> 02:03.891
[Beth S] I do give a fuck, Tami.

02:03.990 --> 02:06.493
I care very much about Tami,

02:06.593 --> 02:10.698
and the fact that she doesn't
believe me, it hurts.

02:10.798 --> 02:12.865
I just love that you are, like,
opening up,

02:12.966 --> 02:15.468
and I was getting
to know you and...

02:15.568 --> 02:17.704
Okay, well, that's gone, girl.

02:17.805 --> 02:19.673
[chuckles]

02:20.508 --> 02:23.544
[Tami] I wasn't angry,
I was hurt.

02:23.644 --> 02:25.312
The fact that Beth A and Glen

02:25.413 --> 02:27.146
come to talk to me
in the kitchen,

02:27.247 --> 02:28.882
you know, I thought
one of them other bitches

02:28.981 --> 02:30.350
was gonna get up off the couch.

02:30.450 --> 02:34.153
But I found a new level
of respect for Beth A,

02:34.254 --> 02:36.189
because she was the one person
who came over

02:36.289 --> 02:37.324
and said, "I heard you."

02:37.425 --> 02:39.158
We good, girl.

02:39.259 --> 02:41.495
[Beth S] I've tried to take
this opportunity

02:41.594 --> 02:43.563
to get to know everyone,

02:43.663 --> 02:45.699
but as far as I'm concerned,

02:45.799 --> 02:50.471
Tami is not interested in really
having a relationship with me.

02:50.570 --> 02:53.173
And I don't... I don't know
what to do right now.

02:53.274 --> 02:55.376
I don't know...
I don't know what to say.

02:57.344 --> 02:58.711
[groans]

03:13.693 --> 03:16.597
-[Irene] Why are you crying?
-[Beth S] Tami's upset.

03:16.697 --> 03:17.931
She says she doesn't trust me.

03:18.031 --> 03:19.400
I don't think she trusts
anybody right now.

03:19.500 --> 03:21.134
'Cause she doesn't trust us.

03:21.235 --> 03:22.802
Well, let her not trust us.

03:22.902 --> 03:24.837
What, am I...
We're supposed to force her to?

03:24.937 --> 03:26.373
No, I understand that,

03:26.473 --> 03:29.342
but I was really enjoying
to get to know her.

03:29.443 --> 03:30.943
It's still not over.

03:31.044 --> 03:34.414
I know, but she's like...
Her wall's back up again, so...

03:35.848 --> 03:37.317
You know what?

03:37.418 --> 03:38.918
She's just gonna go on
with her life, and I get that.

03:39.019 --> 03:40.353
Tomorrow, she might feel
differently.

03:40.454 --> 03:42.055
I'm not gonna let it hurt
my feelings.

03:42.155 --> 03:44.024
You should not let it hurt
your feelings either.

03:44.123 --> 03:45.959
We're grown-ass women
right now, okay, so...

03:46.058 --> 03:47.860
I know, but I mean,
it's just not true.

03:47.961 --> 03:49.763
I mean, I care about her deeply,

03:49.862 --> 03:51.764
and it took a lot of bravery

03:51.865 --> 03:54.367
to share what she shared
with us.

03:55.603 --> 03:56.736
[sighs]

03:56.836 --> 03:58.004
Beth S just seems like

03:58.104 --> 04:00.240
she wants to be accepted
by everybody.

04:00.341 --> 04:03.075
I think she's just expecting
a little too much.

04:03.175 --> 04:05.445
I would love to know
why she feels

04:05.545 --> 04:08.048
the need to have Tami
like her so much.

04:08.147 --> 04:10.984
Why do you need that so bad?

04:11.084 --> 04:12.819
I mean, there's a lot
of other people in the house

04:12.919 --> 04:14.754
that really love Beth S.

04:14.854 --> 04:17.057
Why is it this one person

04:17.156 --> 04:19.091
she needs to have acceptance
from?

04:19.192 --> 04:21.362
I'm sorry you feel that way,
okay?

04:25.098 --> 04:26.867
[light music playing]

04:26.966 --> 04:28.935
[sighs]

04:36.509 --> 04:42.316
* I am the sun and the Earth *

04:42.415 --> 04:45.552
[Beth A] Right now,
I feel a little exhausted.

04:46.553 --> 04:48.120
Didn't sleep last night.

04:49.088 --> 04:52.225
You can imagine
there's lights on everywhere,

04:52.326 --> 04:57.230
and I got these ridiculous
little eyelash extensions.

04:57.331 --> 04:59.533
It's like having a face mask.

05:02.470 --> 05:03.803
Yeah, I did it to myself.

05:03.903 --> 05:05.204
-How'd you sleep?
-I didn't sleep.

05:05.305 --> 05:07.107
The lights are bright,
so it made me be on.

05:07.206 --> 05:08.576
Yeah.

05:08.675 --> 05:10.411
So then I could hear the rhythm
of Glen's snoring.

05:10.511 --> 05:12.079
[David and Beth A laugh]

05:12.178 --> 05:13.814
[Beth A] It was nice to be done
with the day,

05:13.913 --> 05:15.516
get some rest after all that.

05:15.615 --> 05:17.651
[David] I was so glad yesterday
was over, I was so drained.

05:17.750 --> 05:19.319
[Beth A] I'm sure you were.

05:19.420 --> 05:22.322
What emotional roller coaster
are we gonna ride on today?

05:22.423 --> 05:24.824
[David] I woke up so dehydrated
this morning.

05:24.925 --> 05:27.226
-Good morning.
-Good morning.

05:27.326 --> 05:29.028
[Beth S]
Cheers to a new day, everybody.

05:29.129 --> 05:30.930
So I wake up in the morning,

05:31.031 --> 05:33.199
and I have a lot of anxiety
right now

05:33.300 --> 05:35.334
over how Tami is upset with me.

05:36.536 --> 05:38.204
-Do my eyes look bad?
-Your eyes?

05:38.305 --> 05:40.740
I'm all puffy
from crying yesterday.

05:40.841 --> 05:42.475
-No, they're fine.
-No?

05:42.576 --> 05:44.110
Put a little water on them.
You're fine.

05:44.211 --> 05:46.012
-Okay.
-No, they don't look bad.

05:46.112 --> 05:47.848
But I'm not gonna lose hope
just yet.

05:48.615 --> 05:51.519
I'm gonna keep trying to be
close with her in the house.

05:51.619 --> 05:53.220
Don't let it...

05:53.319 --> 05:54.788
I know, but you know
I'm sensitive.

05:54.887 --> 05:56.255
Yes, but you're letting it.

05:56.355 --> 05:58.191
-No you're right, I did let it.
-Yeah, don't.

05:58.290 --> 06:00.961
'Cause I'm too sensitive.
It's my problem.

06:02.194 --> 06:03.896
[Tami]
Yesterday was a rough one.

06:03.997 --> 06:05.865
Um, but today is a new day.

06:05.966 --> 06:09.970
I think that coexisting
in the house with everybody

06:10.069 --> 06:11.738
is important.

06:11.838 --> 06:14.942
So I'm not trying to talk
about what happened yesterday.

06:15.041 --> 06:16.175
Move on.

06:16.276 --> 06:17.810
We're off of that, right?

06:17.911 --> 06:19.547
Okay, ciao, that's it,

06:19.646 --> 06:22.949
we're gonna see
what today brings

06:23.050 --> 06:26.519
in the L.A. Real World House.

06:27.721 --> 06:30.156
[Glen] Where are you going?
Go ahead, sit there.

06:30.257 --> 06:32.024
I am. I'm sitting.
I just wanted to look

06:32.125 --> 06:34.261
-at the view for half a second.
-Oh.

06:34.360 --> 06:35.896
You know, it's not Hawaii,

06:35.995 --> 06:39.066
but it sure is beautiful
in its own way.

06:43.336 --> 06:44.605
[Jon] Look at us all buddies,

06:44.704 --> 06:46.305
just sitting around
in the beach house.

06:46.406 --> 06:48.875
-I know, this is trippy.
-This is really weird, isn't it?

06:48.975 --> 06:50.543
I'm just kind of
taking it all in.

06:50.644 --> 06:53.613
Tami was very upset
and disappointed with me.

06:53.713 --> 06:55.247
I'm just gonna do whatever I can

06:55.348 --> 06:59.819
to kind of, like, deflate
this thing and, like, move on.

06:59.920 --> 07:01.454
Is Mom bringing some...

07:01.555 --> 07:03.723
[laughter]

07:03.824 --> 07:05.625
Some paper towels, is she?

07:05.725 --> 07:07.528
[Irene] Mom's here
with her paper towels.

07:07.627 --> 07:09.463
Now, you're not gonna be
calling me Mom anymore, right?

07:09.562 --> 07:11.331
[Jon] Tami just told Beth
not to call you Mom,

07:11.430 --> 07:13.165
-and then she called you Mom.
-No, Beth can. Jon can.

07:13.266 --> 07:14.434
[Beth A] That's just weird.

07:14.535 --> 07:15.968
-It is.
-That's just weird.

07:16.069 --> 07:17.771
-[laughs]
-[Jon] Tami just said to not...

07:17.870 --> 07:19.038
I don't like it.

07:19.139 --> 07:21.240
Like, you 80.

07:21.341 --> 07:23.610
[laughs]

07:23.711 --> 07:27.213
I feel like
the blanket-pulling incident,

07:27.314 --> 07:28.882
it needed to be talked about.

07:28.981 --> 07:32.218
That stuff stuck with them,
that stuck with them for life.

07:32.319 --> 07:33.586
Yeah, we didn't know
what it was.

07:33.687 --> 07:36.656
When I saw the drama
that happened before me,

07:36.757 --> 07:39.492
'cause I hadn't watched
those episodes before,

07:39.593 --> 07:42.129
I realized why Glen and I
were so close.

07:43.096 --> 07:44.396
[Tami] They are under the table.

07:44.497 --> 07:45.832
[Jon] They're gonna roll around
under the table,

07:45.932 --> 07:47.466
let them roll around
under the table.

07:47.567 --> 07:49.201
[Beth A] You would think
being some of the few people

07:49.302 --> 07:50.838
that will ever
have this experience

07:50.937 --> 07:52.939
in their whole life,
that we would all be family,

07:53.040 --> 07:55.274
kind of like how
the New York show was.

07:55.975 --> 07:58.211
But they were done
getting to know each other,

07:58.310 --> 07:59.713
they'd already come
to the conclusion

07:59.812 --> 08:01.781
that they didn't have tolerance
for each other.

08:01.882 --> 08:03.983
[Jon] Right as we were
checking out of the resort,

08:04.084 --> 08:05.485
Beth A and Tami
really got into it.

08:05.586 --> 08:08.021
Fucking lighten up.
I'm serious, man.

08:08.120 --> 08:10.591
-I did lighten up.
-So ridiculous.

08:10.690 --> 08:12.358
Let's go back
to high school, Tami.

08:12.459 --> 08:14.627
-Give me a fucking break.
-I know, so why don't you

08:14.728 --> 08:16.463
-stop acting like it?
-Oh, my God.

08:16.564 --> 08:18.699
Stop talking to me, okay?
'Cause I've had enough.

08:18.798 --> 08:20.233
Just stop.

08:20.332 --> 08:22.870
Unfortunately, when the seven
of us get together,

08:22.970 --> 08:24.403
at least one person

08:24.504 --> 08:26.406
has to get into an argument
with somebody else.

08:26.505 --> 08:28.375
We didn't know what the vibe...
where the vibe came from,

08:28.475 --> 08:30.276
and now we know when we came,

08:30.377 --> 08:32.546
why we felt the way we felt,

08:32.645 --> 08:35.081
because that was lingering,
and we had no idea what it was,

08:35.182 --> 08:36.182
because we weren't here.

08:36.283 --> 08:38.085
No wonder Tami was shut down.

08:39.787 --> 08:41.955
Oh, my God,
wait a minute though.

08:42.054 --> 08:43.090
[Jon] The eight ball.

08:43.890 --> 08:46.525
Dominic and I were playing
with this eight ball.

08:47.460 --> 08:51.230
We asked if Jon
was going to get laid.

08:51.331 --> 08:53.265
-Well, ask me.
-You might be offended.

08:53.365 --> 08:54.802
Well, then, don't ask me.

08:54.902 --> 08:56.336
[Jon] We're gonna have
a great experience here

08:56.436 --> 08:58.138
at this homecoming.

08:58.238 --> 08:59.239
Say it out loud.

08:59.338 --> 09:00.807
Outlook not so good.

09:00.908 --> 09:03.309
[laughs]

09:03.409 --> 09:07.114
[Jon] There's the Tami laugh.
There's the Tami laugh.

09:07.214 --> 09:08.716
Let's quit asking this.

09:08.816 --> 09:11.250
Yes, we are gonna have
a great experience.

09:11.350 --> 09:13.754
[Irene] So what have you
been up to, David?

09:13.854 --> 09:15.087
Surviving ICU.

09:15.187 --> 09:17.758
-[laughs]
-[Beth S] What happened?

09:18.859 --> 09:22.162
I was riding my bike
going through, uh, Downtown L.A.

09:22.261 --> 09:24.697
-Okay.
-I'm in the bike path,

09:24.798 --> 09:27.668
and I don't know
where this truck just hits me,

09:27.768 --> 09:28.769
and leaves me there.

09:28.869 --> 09:30.102
So I wake up in ICU.

09:30.202 --> 09:31.705
-They had to...
-Damn.

09:31.804 --> 09:33.306
-...drill a hole in my skull...
-[Beth S] Oh, my God.

09:33.405 --> 09:35.375
...'cause the bone was about
to poke my brain.

09:35.475 --> 09:36.777
-You see all these?
-Oh, no.

09:36.876 --> 09:38.144
[Irene]
That's the scar right there?

09:38.245 --> 09:39.779
[David] Yeah.

09:39.879 --> 09:42.481
[Irene] David has been
struggling through a lot.

09:42.581 --> 09:44.183
He's got this huge dent
in his head.

09:44.283 --> 09:46.986
He told me he had a broken
clavicle, a broken wrist,

09:47.086 --> 09:49.522
I think maybe some broken ribs,

09:49.623 --> 09:53.259
and I was really amazed that
he's able to be with us today.

09:53.360 --> 09:54.961
[David] I used to have dreads,

09:55.062 --> 09:57.730
so I woke up in the ICU
with just, like, three dreads,

09:57.831 --> 09:58.865
'cause they had to...

09:58.966 --> 10:00.332
[chuckles]

10:00.432 --> 10:01.735
You're gonna still do comedy?

10:01.835 --> 10:04.571
Yeah, yeah, I'm gonna,
uh, go back on the road,

10:04.672 --> 10:06.840
and living off my savings,
and draining all this,

10:06.940 --> 10:08.741
and the work
ain't coming in, like you...

10:08.841 --> 10:10.576
My God, it was just so...

10:11.510 --> 10:13.145
I'm itching to bounce back

10:13.245 --> 10:15.282
-and make some real money, so...
-Yeah, yeah.

10:15.381 --> 10:16.683
Aw, well, that's great

10:16.783 --> 10:18.618
that you're gonna go back out
on the road.

10:18.719 --> 10:20.153
-That's great.
-Yeah, yeah.

10:20.253 --> 10:21.520
[Irene]
Jon, what have you been up to?

10:21.620 --> 10:22.789
I'm a youth pastor.
I work at a church.

10:22.889 --> 10:24.957
-I lead worship on Sundays.
-Amen.

10:25.057 --> 10:26.426
-[Irene] Mm-hmm.
-[Jon] Love it.

10:26.525 --> 10:27.760
And you've been doing that
for a while, right?

10:27.860 --> 10:29.296
[Jon] 22 years.

10:29.395 --> 10:31.530
I don't know that all
of my roommates know

10:31.630 --> 10:34.167
the extent of my ministry.

10:34.267 --> 10:37.470
Since the show, I actually
returned back to Kentucky

10:37.570 --> 10:39.605
the day the first episode aired.

10:39.706 --> 10:43.076
It was like I was really famous
in the early '90s.

10:43.176 --> 10:45.378
I was doing concerts,
and it was strictly

10:45.477 --> 10:47.647
because they'd seen me
on this reality show.

10:47.748 --> 10:49.548
They hadn't heard
any of my music.

10:49.649 --> 10:52.219
Next Saturday night, I'm gonna
be at the Capitol Music Hall.

10:52.318 --> 10:53.821
Y'all come out and see me,
would you?

10:53.921 --> 10:55.923
After that, I was on the first
Challenge ever.

10:56.889 --> 10:59.525
I was on Battle of the Seasons:
Inferno II.

10:59.625 --> 11:01.193
I was really enjoying life.

11:01.293 --> 11:03.330
I'm gonna bring all of these
people in to have fun with us.

11:03.429 --> 11:06.767
* Some would say I was
A lost man in a lost world *

11:06.866 --> 11:09.469
When my country music career
didn't happen in the '90s,

11:09.568 --> 11:10.870
the attention wore off.

11:10.971 --> 11:12.905
People forgot
that you were this cool,

11:13.005 --> 11:14.474
hip, reality star.

11:14.573 --> 11:17.376
* I lost my faith
In the people on TV *

11:17.476 --> 11:19.245
That was hard to deal with.

11:19.346 --> 11:20.547
You were just a normal dude

11:20.647 --> 11:22.149
that needed to go
get a job again.

11:22.249 --> 11:24.317
And so I immediately went
to work at a church

11:24.417 --> 11:26.986
and became a youth pastor.

11:27.086 --> 11:31.423
* If I ever lose my faith
In you *

11:31.524 --> 11:33.059
These guys,
they're my support group.

11:33.159 --> 11:34.494
When I was young growing up,

11:34.594 --> 11:36.696
I had a lot of mentors
in the church,

11:36.797 --> 11:39.966
and it really laid a foundation
of Christ in my life.

11:40.067 --> 11:42.001
And I'm a mentor
to young people now.

11:42.101 --> 11:44.937
When I was just a little bit
older than you guys,

11:45.038 --> 11:46.505
I was on this television show.

11:46.605 --> 11:48.741
We lived in a house together
with people

11:48.841 --> 11:51.577
that were nothing like me, and
I also was nothing like them.

11:51.677 --> 11:54.447
I have enough young people
to mentor

11:54.547 --> 11:56.582
and to be a father figure
to them.

11:56.682 --> 11:58.485
That's fulfilling my life.

11:58.585 --> 12:01.955
I don't drink alcohol.
I don't live a promiscuous life.

12:02.054 --> 12:05.258
I try not to give in
to the desires of the flesh.

12:05.357 --> 12:08.528
People say, "Aren't you, like,
missing something?"

12:08.628 --> 12:12.164
No, I'm surrounded by people
all the time.

12:12.264 --> 12:14.201
I'm a people person.

12:14.301 --> 12:16.469
I'm pretty happy.

12:17.437 --> 12:19.773
When are you gonna
get married, Jon?

12:20.774 --> 12:21.774
[Jon] I-I'm good.

12:21.875 --> 12:23.143
-[laughter]
-[David] Right.

12:23.243 --> 12:24.411
I mean, uh...

12:24.510 --> 12:25.846
You still a virgin?

12:25.946 --> 12:28.048
-Am I still a virgin? Yes.
-[Tami] You are?

12:28.148 --> 12:29.917
[Jon] Yeah, I'm following
the Lord wholeheartedly.

12:30.017 --> 12:33.153
-I'm all in. I'm all in.
-Oh, my God, that is so good.

12:33.253 --> 12:35.923
I didn't understand it back
when we came through this house

12:36.023 --> 12:37.624
-the first time.
-[Jon] No, you did not.

12:37.724 --> 12:39.860
[Tami] But I can definitely
relate now,

12:39.960 --> 12:41.995
